### Update `next.config` for `proxy`-related flags in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/upgrading/version-16.mdx

This configuration snippet updates `next.config.ts` or `next.config.js` to use the new `skipProxyUrlNormalize` flag, replacing the deprecated `skipMiddlewareUrlNormalize`. This change is part of the broader renaming from `middleware` to `proxy` in Next.js 16, reflecting the new terminology for routing configuration.

```typescript
import type { NextConfig } from 'next'

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  skipProxyUrlNormalize: true,
}

export default nextConfig
```

```javascript
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  skipProxyUrlNormalize: true,
}

module.exports = nextConfig
```

--------------------------------

### Rename Next.js `middleware` function to `proxy`

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/upgrading/version-16.mdx

This snippet demonstrates renaming the `middleware` named export function to `proxy` in both TypeScript and JavaScript files. This aligns with the deprecation of the `middleware` function name in Next.js 16, ensuring proper function identification for the new `proxy` system.

```typescript
export function proxy(request: Request) {}
```

```javascript
export function proxy(request) {}
```

--------------------------------

### Rename Next.js `middleware` file to `proxy`

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/upgrading/version-16.mdx

This shell command renames the `middleware.ts` or `middleware.js` file to `proxy.ts` or `proxy.js` respectively. This change reflects the deprecation of the `middleware` filename in Next.js 16, clarifying its role in network boundary and routing focus. The `proxy` runtime is `nodejs` and does not support `edge`.

```bash
# Rename your middleware file
mv middleware.ts proxy.ts
# or
mv middleware.js proxy.js
```

