### Migrate Next.js Middleware to Proxy Convention

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/upgrading/codemods.mdx

This codemod facilitates the migration of Next.js projects from the deprecated `middleware` convention to the `proxy` convention in Next.js 16. It renames files (e.g., `middleware.ts` to `proxy.ts`), named exports, and several Next.js configuration properties to align with the new naming scheme.

```bash
npx @next/codemod@latest middleware-to-proxy .
```

```typescript
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'

export function middleware() {
  return NextResponse.next()
}
```

```typescript
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'

export function proxy() {
  return NextResponse.next()
}
```

