### Proxy API Requests using Next.js Rewrites in `next.config.ts`

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/migrating/from-create-react-app.mdx

This `next.config.ts` example demonstrates how to configure Next.js rewrites to proxy API requests. It replaces the `proxy` field functionality from CRA's `package.json`, allowing requests to a specified source path to be forwarded to a different destination URL.

```ts
import { NextConfig } from 'next'

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  async rewrites() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/api/:path*',
        destination: 'https://your-backend.com/:path*',
      },
    ]
  },
}
```

